1. e4 d5 ({The champion of rare continuations!  The Scandinavian Defense is stronger than} 1... Nf6 {, g6 , Nc6 , and some other fun lines.   In this Quickstarter, we will focus only on the most popular Scandinavian lines, so you can go out and start crushing souls after just one hour of studying the theory.   Once you're ready to dive deeper, begin with the chapters #1 & #2 .}) 2. Nc3 dxe4 {Simple and good.} (2... d4 3. Nce2 e5 4. c3 {. This setup is what White wants with this sideline.}) 3. Nxe4 Nc6 (3... Qd5 $5 4. Nc3 Qa5 {. Try this if you insist on the main lines or want to see your opponent smile.}) 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Nxf6+ exf6 6. d4 Bd6 {This setup is a dream position for any Caro-Kann player. Black has healthy development, and the double pawns extra shelter the king.} *

