1. e4 d5 ({The champion of rare continuations!  The Scandinavian Defense is stronger than} 1... Nf6 {, g6 , Nc6 , and some other fun lines.   In this Quickstarter, we will focus only on the most popular Scandinavian lines, so you can go out and start crushing souls after just one hour of studying the theory.   Once you're ready to dive deeper, begin with the chapters #1 & #2 .}) 2. exd5 {The main move - White wants to punish you for bringing out the queen so early and win some tempos.} Qxd5 3. Nf3 ({This move is the most serious alternative to} 3. Nc3 {. White wants to play c4 and only then continue with Nc3 , thus forming a strong pawn center. Of course, there's also a fair chance your opponent will randomly develop the kingside knight first, but they don't know any opening theory.}) 3... Bg4 4. Be2 Nc6 {You start so aggressively to talk White out of playing d4 . If you succeed and they do something else, you can castle long and push ... e5 yourself, effectively fighting for advantage.} 5. d4 {The main move.} O-O-O 6. c3 {White can't afford to be so slow - there's a fair chance that Black will take over the game in the next several moves.} e5 7. c4 Qe4 8. Nc3 Bb4 9. d5 Nf6 {Black has a very dynamic position.} *

