an.} Bg4 8. f3 Be6 {Now the white knight on h4 is weird.} 9. f4 g6 10. Bd3 Bg4 {Now that White has committed to Bd3 , the timing for ... Bg4 is perfect.} 11. Nf3 Nbd7 12. h3 Bf5 {If Black trades the light-squared bishops, White might experience some problems with the light squares.} 13. Bc4 h5 14. Qe2 Qc7 15. O-O-O e6 {Leading to a complex game where Black has a lot of ideas.} *

