9... Qd8 {One key element to becoming a great Scandinavian player is understanding how long you can keep your queen on a5 and resist the temptation to retreat 'just to be safe.' In general, if nobody is bothering your queen, you better keep it there, but you always want to ensure you're not missing either one of the discovered attacks of the white knight or the d5 push.} 10. Nxf6+ Qxf6 11. Nxd7 Kxd7 {The black king on d7 is surprisingly safe – Black can artificially castle long.} *

