22... Ne4 {If your opponent made it this far, they are well prepared. In the course, we mention several times that White can fight for a considerable space advantage by pushing f4 , which also stops Black's typical counterplay with ... e5 . Make sure you can activate your pieces by a pawn sacrifice. Otherwise, you will be very passive with no counterplay.} 23. Bxe4 dxe4 24. Qxe4 f5 {Sometimes you might have to sacrifice a second pawn on e6 as well.} 25. gxf5 Rxf5 {Black has sufficient compensation for the lost pawn.} *

