11... Nxe5 {In these lines, it's important to understand when you can capture on e5 . It's directly tied with White's plan to play f4 - f5 – if White can't do it right away, you're safe.} 12. dxe5 Nd5 {Sometimes the knight can go to d7 as well, targeting the e5 -pawn.} 13. Nxd5 Bxd2+ 14. Rxd2 cxd5 {Even if White prevents Black from castling, the center is too solid for Black's king to be in danger.} *

