11... Nxe5 {Whenever White has the knight on e5 and threatens with g4 , make sure you can take on e5 . A key detail is where White's light-squared bishop stands.} 12. gxf5 Nxc4 {If the bishop is already on b3 , you're in trouble.} 13. Qxc4 Bxc3 14. Qxc3 O-O-O {With a balanced position.} *

