11... h5 {This idea is borrowed from the Sicilian Najdorf – don't be afraid to be bold and stop White's kingside ambitions. What makes it truly amazing is that you can play this move also after castling short. While White will attempt to pick up your h-pawn, you will get a lot of counterplay on the queenside.} *

