12... Na6 {As you will see, sometimes the Scandinavian Defense very much feels like the Tartakower variation from the Caro-Kann Defense (everything ... exf6 related).   The queenside knight often enters the game via a6 rather than d7 . The reason may be that on d7 , it blocks the view of the queen, and later on b6 , it might feel quite clumsy, but on a6 , the knight is not crossing paths with anyone. The knight can later be positioned on c7 and fight for the d5 -square with ... b5 push or also ... Ne6 looks interesting.} *

