13... Bc8 ({The 'automatic'} 13... Bg6 {leads to big trouble since White will trade the bishop and quickly open the h-file with the h4 - h5 push. However, the bishop on c8 stands better than on d7 for a good reason.}) 14. Bd3 Na6 15. Qh5 g6 16. Nxg6 fxg6 17. Bxg6 Qc7 {That's why the bishop retreated to c8 – not to block the queen, but to let it defend the h7 -pawn.} *

