{✱ Note: Be cautious of the Bg4 threat.} 7. Be3 {If White plays like this, they force Black to win the d-pawn. Otherwise, some of Black's earlier choices might be questionable.} Bxf3 8. Bxf3 Nxd4 {This maneuver features two tricks.} 9. Bxd4 (9. Bg4 {. Make sure you never miss this shot.} Nc2+ $1 10. Qxc2 Qxg4 {, and Black keeps the extra pawn.}) 9... Qe6+ {A very important check. Otherwise, Black won't be able to win back the piece.} (9... e5 $4 {– find out why yourself*, even grandmasters make such blunders.}) 10. Be2 c5 {Black wins back the piece.} *

