7... e6 {In this critical variation, the move order is significant – we're highlighting one of the mistakes.} (7... Nbd7 $1 {. Black deals with the Ne5 possibility and makes sure that at the moment the Nd5 jump is not dangerous.}) 8. Nd5 Qd8 9. Nxf6+ {The point is that with both captures on f6 , Black experiences problems.} Qxf6 10. Qe2 Nd7 11. O-O-O {Now Black should watch out for the d5 push.} Be7 12. Bg5 Qg6 13. Bxe7 Kxe7 {Black will have to survive with an exposed king – maybe with perfect play, it's possible, but it's not a fun way to play.} *

