[PlyCount "6"]
[GameId "2174210255672063"]

11... O-O {You might think you can meet White's g4 by capturing on e5 , but things are much different with the king on g8 .} (11... b5 $1 {. Before castling or capturing on e5 , here, it's important to define the placement of White's light-squared bishop. If it goes to b3 , you immediately start a queenside attack with ... a5 .} 12. Bd3 Bxd3 13. Nxd3 {. Now White's f4 feels like a waste of time since g4 - g5 is much slower without the light-squared bishop on f5 or g6 .} b4 14. Ne4 {. The knight can't block the a-pawn's advancement due to ... Qa5 and ... Nb6 .} a5 {. Black is doing great and already can castle short.}) 12. g4 Nxe5 13. fxe5 Nxg4 ({Better was} 13... Bxg4 14. Qg2 Bxd1 15. exf6 Bxf6 16. Rxd1 Bxd4 {to get a rook and a couple of pawns for two minor pieces.}) 14. Rdg1 {Now White's attack on the kingside is killing.} *

