11... b5 {This is a typical idea in the variation, and you can mix it up if the white bishop stands on c4 - you want to push the pawn on b5 and back it up with ... Nb6 the next move. Unfortunately, this does not work here.} (11... O-O-O {is the best that Black can do.}) 12. d5 {That's why White played Bb3 earlier – to avoid Black's ... b5 . Black's position is terrible.} *

