8... Bg6 {Another example of an 'automatic' retreat to g6 . It would be standard if it were not for some specific details.} (8... Bg4 {is a sharper continuation.} 9. f3 Qh5 {. The point – instead of the automatic retreat to h5 , Black hits the knight. Remember, this maneuver might be useful in similar positions.} 10. g3 Bh3 {. The arising positions are very complex that not everyone might enjoy – Black makes many moves with the queen.}) (8... e6 {is the easiest choice – Black can just ignore White's threat and continue development.}) 9. g4 {Once more, recognize the dangers of White's aggressive pawn pushes on the kingside. The black queen on a5 here is misplaced.} e6 10. g5 {That's the idea – there's no jump to d5 .} Nh5 11. Be2 {The black knight is trapped.} *

