10... Bg6 {One more example when the 'automatic' retreat is terrible.} (10... Bd5 $6 11. Bd3 $1 {. Black has problems with the bishop. Most likely, Black will have to get rid of the knight from g5 and go back with the bishop on e4 , which loses time.}) (10... e6 $1 {. Black deals with the hidden threats and gives up the light-squared bishop for a solid game.}) 11. f4 e6 12. f5 {Suddenly, Black has no satisfactory moves!} Bh5 (12... exf5 13. Nxf5 $1 {. The point.} Bxf5 14. Bxf7+ Ke7 15. Qe2+ Kd6 16. Bf4+ {, with a brutal mate.}) 13. fxe6 Bxd1 {Ends the game immediately, but Black is doomed anyway.} 14. exf7+ Ke7 15. Nf5# {Legal's mate on the board!} *

