6... Bf5 {There's a reason why White played Bd3 before – they anticipate your ... Bf5 move.} (6... Bg4 {. The light-squared bishop needs some attention, so the g4 -square is the only good option.} 7. f3 Bh5 {. Because of the white bishop on d3 , Black's ... Bg4 - h5 - g6 now makes perfect sense. Normally you would refrain from developing the bishop on g4 , but this is an exception.}) 7. b4 {That's why!} *

