6... c6 {With the knight on b5 , you should suspect that your opponent is trying some cheap tricks. And you'd be right – because that’s precisely what they’re doing!} (6... Nf6 {is a simple and promising way to deal with White's threats.} 7. Bb2 a6 {.}) 7. Bxf7+ Kxf7 8. Qh5+ {And no matter what Black will respond next, the queen is lost.} g6 9. Nd6+ exd6 10. Qxa5 {Black is just lost.} *

