7... Nxd4 {If you want to capture the d4 -pawn in any Scandinavian variations, do it carefully. Here, it's a mistake.} (7... e6 $1 {. Black continues the development but keeps a close eye on the d4 -pawn.} 8. h3 {. White forces matters. If they castle short, Black could still revisit the idea of capturing on d4 or proceed with the typical ... h5 plan.} Bxf3 {, and after} 9. Nxf3 Qa5+ $1 {is an essential check to which White doesn't have a satisfactory answer.}) 8. Nxd4 Rxd4 9. f3 {The bishop is trapped.} *

