n.}) 23. Bc2 Rae8 24. Rbe1 Re6 {Black is about to build a blockade to protect the king. We can stop our analysis here, since the game is not forcing. You're considering playing next ... g6 and a positional sacrifice like ... Ne4 should be under your radar to compensate for the missing pawn by targeting the weaknesses on the queenside. Alternatively, you can go for a center counter-attack with ... d4 .} ({After} 24... h6 {, the game could continue:} 25. g6 {Qg2} Rd8 {f4 White is charging on the kingside; thus, generating some counterplay in the center is important. Bb6} 26. Kh2 {Qc7 . Freeing the c6 -square for the black rook. Rf1 Rc6 Be1} Ne4 {pushing ... d4 also looks interesting.} 27. Bxe4 dxe4 28. Rxe4 Ba5 {, White has the extra pawn but the queenside pawns are weak, and the black king is safe.}) *

