ike to position the knight on c4 but if White denies you the opportunity, think about moves like ... Bb8 , ... Nc8 - d6 . It's unclear if White can improve the threat of Bxh7 since Black is always ready to open the kingside with ... fxg5 and the battery with... Qd6 , generating some serious threats.} 22. Rae1 Nc4 23. Bc1 fxg5 {White's been playing smart; it's time to clarify the situation in the center.} 24. fxg5 e5 {The position remains double-edged. White has the two bishops in an open position, but the weak king keeps the status quo.} ({After Rxf8+ , this is how the game might continue: Rxf8} 24... Rxf1+ {exd4 cxd4 Qc8 Rxf8+ Bxf8 Bf5 Qe8 . Now that the storm has passed, Black is thinking about their attacking ideas.}) *

