rete solution.} 20. Qb5 {The human move.} (20. Bxf6 {. The engine entertains us with some sharp and funny lines.} Qxa4 $1 21. g4 $3 {. The point is to sacrifice the bishop on g7 and use the g-file together with Qe5 + for a strong attack.} Bg6 $1 22. Qc4 {. The only move.} gxf6 23. dxc5 Rac8 {. The position is equal – human beings don't think like this.} 24. Rd6 Rxc5 {. Not forced but looks interesting.} 25. Qxc5 Qxa2 26. f4 Qa1+ 27. Kd2 Qxb2 28. f5 exf5 29. gxf5 Bxf5 30. Qxf5 Qc3+ 31. Kd1 Qa1+ 32. Kd2 Qc3+ {. With a perpetual check.}) 20... cxd4 21. Bxf6 Qc7 {A powerful intermezzo move that comes with further tricks.} 22. Qc4 Qf4+ 23. Rd2 gxf6 24. Qxd4 Qh6 {Visually, Black looks slightly better since White cannot exploit the weakened black king.} *

