g5 $1 {. This idea is important to know – the problem is that the jump on d5 now is impossible.} Nh5 14. Bxe6 {. White crashes through.}) 11. Nxg6 {The most popular continuation in the position, after which White will have several interesting continuations at their disposal.} hxg6 12. d5 {For some time, the popular belief was that White here has very good chances for an advantage, but the practice of recent years has proven that Black does well.} cxd5 13. Bxd5 {Taking with the bishop is not dangerous.} Nxd5 14. Nxd5 Qc6 15. Bc3 Rh5 {White seemingly has a nice centralized knight but can't keep it there.} 16. Ne3 Rc8 {Black has at least equalized – the king feels safe in the center.} *

