nificant counterplay on the queenside with} b3 {.}) 22... e5 {White's passed d-pawn will be blockaded, but White's weak kingside pawns give Black full compensation for the missing pawn.} ({Rde1 . Here's how the game might continue:} 22... Rh5 {Re4 Rc8 Rg1 Rf5} 23. Be1 Bh6+ {, and White's extra pawn doesn't feel to be significant.}) *

