 falling apart.}) 15... c5 {Black's lead in development gives him full compensation for the missing pawn.} ({After Be3 , the game might continue: cxd4 Bxd4} 15... Nxe5 {Bxe5} 16. Qb4 {Black forces the queens off the board, but the white king is weak. Kf1 . Blocking with the bishop on c3 would ruin White's queenside pawn structure forever, making them easy targets.} Ne4 17. a3 {Bc5 Bd4} Nxd2 $1 18. Nxd2 {Bxd4 , and Black starts to take over the game.}) *

