1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qa5 4. d4 Nf6 5. Nf3 c6 {In this chapter, we will look at some harmless continuations and what to do if your opponent develops their pieces like the 'Fritz 5' chess engine or is a big fan of online bullet games.} 6. Bd3 {This is the only move in this chapter requiring extra attention. No wonder some strong players have also been testing it.} Bg4 {Normally, you don't put the bishop on g4 , but this variation is an exception. The reason is that White's h3 - g4 and Ne5 are not as good as they are in the classical variation.} (6... Bf5 $6 {. White's idea reveals in this variation.} 7. b4 $1 {The point.} Qxb4 {Black has to accept the pawn.} 8. Bxf5 Qxc3+ 9. Bd2 Qc4 10. Bd3 Qe6+ 11. Kf1 {. For the sacrificed pawn White has a dangerous initiative.}) 7. h3 Bh5 8. g4 {If White plays it straightforwardly, it won't give them any dividends but instead will drastically increase the 'cost of their moves' when any mistake can lead them to a ruined position because of the created weaknesses.} Bg6 {Now White's typical Ne5 and h4 - h5 plan no longer works since the light-squared bishop is on d3 .} 9. g5 {Typical engine suggestion. With the naked eye, you can immediately see the positional drawbacks.} Nd5 10. O-O e6 {Black's moves are standard.} 11. Ne2 Nd7 12. c4 Bxd3 13. Qxd3 Ne7 {Black is about to fianchetto the dark-squared bishop on g7 , anchor the knight on f5 and start pressing the white pawn on d4 .} 14. c5 {White shuts the black queen from joining the kingside, which creates further light-square weaknesses in the position.} Qd8 15. Rd1 h6 {Black uses an opportunity to open the h-file to activate the rook.} 16. h4 hxg5 17. hxg5 Nd5 {The black king on e8 feels safe with the center locked.} 18. Nf4 Be7 19. g6 {White is charging forward with all their army.} Nxf4 20. Bxf4 ({If} 20. gxf7+ {then} Kxf7 21. Bxf4 Nf8 {, and the position remains double-edged.}) 20... Nf8 21. gxf7+ Kxf7 22. Re1 Kg8 23. Qe4 Qe8 {Black has no issues, and if anyone is at risk here, it's White. Comparing the kings, Black's is clearly safer.} *

