ging choice might feel like a blunder.} 11. Bxf7+ {Indeed! Did Black miss this? However, Black just sold the pawn to accelerate their development, and the king on d8 will feel just fine.} Kd8 12. Bb3 Re8+ 13. Be3 Be4 14. Ne2 {White responds energetically, but also Black doesn't have to take the pawn on g2 .} a5 {Black plays like nothing happened, and White has to figure out where to position the king.} 15. O-O {Probably most people who will get this far will castle short. Castling long feels risky due to Black's ... Bg6 and ... Qf5 plan.} a4 16. Bd1 Bg6 {Invitation to repeat the position after Qf3  Be4 .} 17. Qh4 Re4 18. Nf4 Bf5 19. Bf3 Re8 {The white queen is very poorly placed against the ... g5 threat. The engine gives equality, though, and is willing to give up a minor piece for three pawns.} *

