mes of the variation. You probably don't have to study it move by move, but at least going through some ideas wouldn't hurt.} Kxe7 12. Ne2 Nd7 13. Ng3 Bg6 14. O-O Nb6 {Black's moves are very easy.} 15. Bb3 Bxg3 {An interesting choice – Black marked White's dark-squared bishop as a potentially bad piece. The engine prefers pushing forward the a-pawn.} 16. Rfe1+ Kd7 17. hxg3 Rhe8 18. g4 a5 19. a4 Rxe1+ 20. Rxe1 Bd3 {A very nice pawn sacrifice to control the c4 -square.} 21. Bxf7 Bc4 22. Bxc4 Nxc4 23. Bc1 b5 {Black had a very comfortable game in Denis Kadrić (2561) – Miodrag Savić (2406) BIH-chT 20th Neum 2022.} *

