e7 11. Qxe7+ Bxe7 {Slightly more accurate than taking with the king, but the difference isn't groundbreaking.} (11... Kxe7 {. The position should be holdable even if you mix it up.} 12. O-O-O Be6 13. Rhe1 Kd7 14. b3 {. Quite strong.} ({(} 14. Bxe6+ fxe6 15. Re4 Na6 16. c3 Nc7 {. Here Black's setup seems to be rock solid, albeit nobody can argue that White is pressing.) 14... Na6 15.Bxa6 bxa6 16.Ba5 , and White is better.})) 12. O-O-O Be6 {This is always the key idea – the bishop has nothing to do on the h7 - b1 diagonal, and it's better to cover the e-file instead.} 13. b3 b5 14. Bd3 {If White wants to be ambitious, he's avoiding the bishop trade.} O-O 15. Rhe1 Ba3+ 16. Kb1 Na6 17. Be4 Rfc8 {Black's plan is clear – play on the queenside.} *

