1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qa5 4. d4 Nf6 {In this short chapter we will examine some interesting alternatives from White's perspective that shouldn't cause you headaches but still could be important to know.} 5. h3 {These quiet pawn moves sometimes can be poisonous, but it doesn't pose any problems in this particular position. White stops ... Bg4 from happening, but as you already guessed, we wanted to position the bishop on f5 anyway.} Bf5 6. Nf3 c6 7. Bd3 {If White plays something like this, you can always continue with ... e6 , ... Be7 , and castle short, but it also might be a good idea to initiate some favorable trades.} Bxd3 8. Qxd3 Qa6 {If White trades the queens, the position is equal, and White has not included c4 to fight for the center. If White declines, they will have problems to castle short.} *

