d.} ({f4? . Here's how White might immediately make a mistake:} 14... Nxd3 $1 15. cxd3 ({(} 15. Nxg6 Nxb2 16. Qc1 hxg6 17. Qxb2 Ba3 {. White drops the knight on c3 !)}) {Rxd3 Bd2 . The only move, otherwise ... Rxe3 will be too easy.} 15... Bc5 16. Kh2 {Rhd8 Nf3} Bh5 $1 {. Black has a powerful initiative.} 17. Ne4 {Rxd2! Nexd2} Bf3 18. Qxf3 {Rxd2 . After this forced sequence, Black already has a minimal material advantage. Qg3} Bf8 $1 19. Rad1 {Rxd1 Rxd1} Qb6 {. Opposite color bishops give Black good chances for a successful initiative against the white king.}) *

