.  Here is a sample line showing how the game might continue:} 12. Qxe5+ Nxe5 13. Re1 Bc5+ 14. Be3 Bxe3+ 15. Rxe3 Nfg4 16. Rxe5+ Nxe5 17. Re1 f6 18. d4 f4 {.}) 10... O-O-O 11. Qe1 h5 {It's time to organize some counterplay! With the white knight gone from the g3 -square, you no longer need to worry about f5 . Ensure you don't mix up this line with the white knight standing on h4 – then you're missing this resource.} 12. Nge4 Qc7 13. Ng5 Nb6 14. Bb3 Kb8 15. a4 Nbd5 {Black has solved all of their opening problems that involve a counterplay.} *

