e a surprise.} Kxf7 10. Ne5+ Kg8 11. Nxg4 Qxg2 {. Because of this resource, Black is still in the game, but the complications are in White's favor.} 12. Nxf6+ exf6 13. Kd2 Nd7 14. Ne4 Qh3 $1 15. Rg1 {. White has all the fun – their king is much more secure than Black's.}) 9. a4 b6 {It's important to build the battery of the queen and bishop first - White can't play Ne5 because the g2 -pawn is hanging.} (9... Bb4 $6 {. If Black starts with the wrong move order, White will claim the better position.} 10. O-O O-O 11. Ne5 Qd6 12. f4 Nbd7 13. d4 {. Suddenly, Black is quite cramped.} b6 14. Na2 {. The bishop on b4 is in trouble, plus White's Qf3 threat is looming.}) 10. O-O Bb7 {Just in time – now Ne5 is not happening.} 11. Bb3 {White might be tempted to bring back on the table the d4 - d5 push, but he's too slow for that.} Bd6 12. d4 O-O {Black has successfully castled to safety.} 13. Qd3 Nbd7 14. Rad1 Rfe8 {The position is equal.} *

