1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qa5 4. g3 {You will often meet players who instead of 'punishing' Black for choosing the Scandinavian Defense, will want to opt for an easy game. In this chapter, we will talk about everything g3 -related.} Nf6 5. Bg2 e5 {If White doesn't care about the center, you should! Black attempts to play out the opening more aggressively.} 6. Nf3 {The most logical move – White opts for quick development.} Bd6 7. O-O O-O {Now White has a choice between opening the position with d4 or applying pressure against the e5 -pawn with Re1 .} 8. Re1 {White doesn't reveal the cards, are they going to play d3 or d4 ?} Re8 {Black should do the same.} ({If you rush with} 8... Nc6 {, White will continue with} 9. d3 {, and the queen on a5 feels awkward.}) 9. d3 {White is playing some slow chess and hopes that their clear plan gives them a good game. But what about Black? Strangely, previous Chessable courses don't pay enough attention to this strong plan.} c6 {Black limits the scope of White's light-squared bishop on g2 and prepares an escape route for the queen.} 10. h3 {A good move – most of the time, the control of the g4 -square will be important.} h6 {Black can respond with the same logic. Controlling the g5 -square enables the ... Be6 move, followed by ... Nbd7 .} ({If Black plays} 10... Be6 {now, then} 11. Ng5 {threatens to win the bishop pair for no compensation.}) 11. a3 {In this pawn structure keep an eye on White's b4 plans as well.} Be6 12. Nd2 Nbd7 13. Nc4 Bxc4 {It's important to keep the dark-squared bishop because it's about to become quite active.} 14. dxc4 Bc5 15. Bxh6 {Necessary; otherwise, White has good chances to enter a position with a bad light-squared bishop vs a good knight.} gxh6 16. b4 Bxb4 {Good enough – also 16... Qa6 deserves attention.} 17. axb4 Qxb4 18. Qd2 e4 {Much stronger than the 'automatic' ... Kg7 – Black is fighting for activity and space advantage.} 19. Rab1 ({Obviously not} 19. Nxe4 $2 Qxd2 20. Nxd2 Rxe1+ 21. Rxe1 a5 {, and Black has a strong outside passed pawn.}) 19... Qa5 20. Rxb7 Rad8 {Black has a slightly weakened king but good enough counterplay and chances to take over the game.} *

