l players feel comfortable entering such sharp positions where they might get checkmated on the spot.} 10. b5 {. White should not accept the g-pawn; otherwise, the opened g-file will guarantee Black a strong initiative.} Ne7 11. Qa4 Kb8 12. Bc4 Qd7 13. Ne5 Qc8 14. Qb3 {. White is faster with his threats. It doesn't mean this position is not playable for Black – know the risk.}) 6. Bxf3 Qe6+ {Also, Black does not have a great choice – if you keep the queens, White will proceed with c3 - d4 , and Black's ... e5 plan feels soft without the light-squared bishop on the board.} 7. Be2 Nd4 {It's necessary to eliminate White's light-squared bishop before White can play c3 .} 8. c3 Nxe2 9. Qxe2 Qxe2+ 10. Kxe2 e5 11. d3 O-O-O {Black is safe, as seen in the game Liwia Jarocka (2143) – Andrei Skvortsov (2249), Titled Tuesday intern op 20th Dec Late Chess.com INT blitz 2022.} *

