ttack, but not all players feel comfortable entering such sharp positions where they might get checkmated on the spot. A perfect choice in the blitz or rapid format!} 10. Nxg5 {White should not accept the pawn.} Bxe2 11. Qxe2 Rg8 12. b5 {An important intermezzo move to gain access to the e5 -square.} Ne7 13. Qe5 {White has to quickly force the queen trade.} (13. Nf3 $2 Qh5 {. Suddenly, Black has a killing attack!}) 13... Nf5 14. Qxd5 Rxd5 15. Nxf7 {There goes another pawn!} Nh4 16. g3 Ne4 17. Ne5 Bd6 {Black has a strong initiative for the two sacrificed pawns.} ({After Re1 the game could continue:} 17... Rxe5 $1 18. dxe5 Nf3+ {Kf1 Nxe1 Kxe1 Bxe5 , with a compensation for the sacrificed pawn.}) *

