ttack, but not all players feel comfortable entering such sharp positions where they might get checkmated on the spot. A perfect choice in the blitz or rapid format!} 10. b5 {White should not accept the g-pawn; otherwise, the opened g-file will guarantee Black a strong initiative.} (10. Nbd2 {would allow Black to carry out the plan.} g4 11. hxg4 Bxg4 12. b5 $1 Na5 13. Ne5 {. White aims to punish Black's initiative by playing positionally.} Bxe2 14. Qxe2 Bd6 $1 15. Nxf7 Rhg8 {. White already needs to be careful.} 16. Nxd6+ cxd6 17. f3 Rg6 18. Rf2 Kb8 {, and White's extra pawn doesn't play any role – Black has a practical compensation.}) 10... Ne7 11. Qa4 {A principled choice - the other alternative is to play in the center. Now we're entering a race, who will checkmate the opponent's king first.} Kb8 12. Bc4 {Another very accurate move for White.} Qd7 13. Ne5 Qc8 14. Nd2 Nfd5 {You want to get rid of White's knight to push ... g4} 15. Qb3 f6 16. Nd3 g4 17. h4 Nf5 18. g3 {It seems that White has successfully closed the kingside and can finally start their own attack on the queenside.} Bg6 19. a4 {How could we possibly open the kingside?} c5 {Let the madness begin!} 20. dxc5 ({The line starting with} 20. bxc6 {at least looks normal.} Qxc6 21. Re1 Nxc3 $1 22. Qxc3 Nxd4 23. Nf4 e5 24. Nxg6 hxg6 25. Bb2 g5 {, and Black has a terrific initiative.}) 20... Nde3 {It gets completely out of control. Here's the sample line of what might follow.} 21. Bxe6 Qc7 22. Nb4 Nxg3 23. Na6+ {White has no choice!} ({A. Of course,} 23. fxe3 $4 {fails to} Ne2+ 24. Kh1 ({(} 24. Kf2 $4 Qh2+ 25. Ke1 Nxc1 {)}) 24... Qg3 25. Na6+ {, the best try,} Ka8 ({(Always beware of desperate attempts! If} 25... bxa6 $4 26. bxa6+ Ka8 27. Qb7# {. )}) 26. Nc7+ Qxc7 {.}) ({B. If} 23. Re1 $2 Bxc5 $1 {, the game could continue,} 24. Nc6+ ({(The engine line is} 24. a5 Bxb4 25. cxb4 Rd3 {. )}) 24... Ka8 25. Nxd8 Nc2 26. Bd5 Rxd8 {.}) 23... bxa6 24. bxa6+ Ka8 25. fxe3 {Now, they can take the knight.} Qc6 ({With a mating threat:} 25... Z0 {Qh1+} 26. Kf2 {Qh2+ Ke1 Qe2# .}) 26. Qb7+ {The only move which maintains equality.} Qxb7 27. axb7+ Kxb7 {With equality...} *

