Nxd4 Bxe2 9. Qxe2 Rxd4 {Black has won a pawn and now White has to show something for it.} 10. Be3 Rd7 {The difference why the rook stands better on d7 than on d8 is that in some lines, you avoid the Qg4 + and can double the rooks one move faster.} 11. Bxa7 {If White takes the pawn, this gives Black enough time to complete the development.} Nf6 12. Nc3 e6 13. Rad1 Bb4 {Black has completed the development; White can't exploit the slightly exposed black king.} 14. Rxd7 Nxd7 15. Nb5 Rd8 {White has nothing better than to start initiating some trades, leading to an equal endgame.} *

