lack is not interested in losing a piece for nothing.} Bxf3 10. Bxf3 Qe6+ {, and Black is winning.}) 9... Bb4+ 10. Nc3 Bxf3 11. Bxf3 Qc4 {White is simply not getting out of the opening – castling short is not an option and White's center is about to collapse.} 12. Qb3 Qxb3 13. axb3 Nxd4 14. Bxd4 Rxd4 15. Rxa7 {White has managed to keep the material balance, but now the exposed king in the center starts to tell.} Re8+ 16. Kf1 Rd2 {Black is better – the pawn on b7 doesn't matter much.} *

