1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 {In this chapter we will have a closer look at rare continuations on 3rd move.} 3. d4 ({This is quite similar to} 3. Nf3 {, which we discussed in the two previous chapters ( #15 & #16 ) – White wants to get a position with d4 - c4 and Nc3 , avoiding the typical Scandinavian counterplay against the pawn on d4 .}) 3... Nc6 ({More accurate than the immediate} 3... e5 {.}) 4. Nf3 {The main move. Black has to continue aggressively; otherwise, White will punish the ... Nc6 move.} e5 {The simplest and most solid continuation. There's a fair chance that we might still transpose into something from the previous chapter.} 5. Nc3 Bb4 6. Bd2 Bxc3 {All these moves are pretty forced until this point.} 7. Bxc3 e4 8. Ne5 Nxe5 9. dxe5 Ne7 {This endgame has been tested in practice many times – White has nothing here, although they enjoy the bishop pair. White has three main continuations to continue testing Black.} 10. Qe2 {The most played move in the position – White would like to win the e4 -pawn with g3 and Bg2 .} Be6 11. g3 e3 {An important move to know.} 12. f3 O-O-O 13. Qxe3 Qc6 {Black has full compensation for the pawn – either White will lose the e5 -pawn or the bishop on c3 is completely misplaced.} 14. Be2 {White threatens to take the pawn on a7 , but they need to secure their position.} Kb8 {Black is threatening with the simple ... Nd5 .} 15. a4 {White is anticipating Black's ... Nd5 and wants to keep the extra pawn. Plus, Bb5 might be a problem.} a6 16. O-O Nd5 17. Qd4 h5 ({A good moment to remind White that their king is quite vulnerable – it's possible to start also with} 17... g5 {.}) (17... Nxc3 $6 {Here's why White included the a4 move.} 18. Qxc3 Qxc3 19. bxc3 Rd5 20. f4 Rc5 21. Ra3 {. Black has some compensation, but White keeps the pawn and can continue improving the position. Best to steer clear of this line.}) 18. h4 Bf5 {Black has full compensation for the missing pawn – White should be quite careful. It seems that the extra pawn will fall no matter what but going for a kingside attack also looks tempting.} *

